Entries.default: "Our guildmaster traces her heritage back to the first watershapers."
"I pray that the guild can persevere without Mairu."
"Ekenu has a promising future in the guild."
"Did you see the dragon? It flew right over me!"
"Shh. I'm practicing the first form."
The watershaper catches sight of Tekēhu and looks away.
"Are you giving tours now, Tekēhu?"
"I wish that my sculptures were half as lauded as Tekēhu's."
"My focus has been off lately."
"So many of us fallen... and for what?"
"Those nāga will pay."
"How could this happen to us?"
"Curse those snakes..."
"My friends... all gone."
"Why... why us?"
"Hey, stop that!"
The watershaper looks into the distance with a vacant expression.
"Something happened to us after the nāga were dispatched..."
"What... what happened to us?"
"After that latest quake, something feels different."
